Quick Share.
Seamless sharing for billions.1

Share hi-res photos, videos, files, Wi-Fi credentials and more with nearby Android devices in a few taps. It’s fast, more secure and easy to use. Plus, you can Quick Share with anyone on supported ChromeOS and Windows PC devices.2

¹ Based on billions of Android devices worldwide.
² Devices must be within Bluetooth sharing distance and have Wi-Fi enabled. Works with compatible devices.

Share with your Windows PC

Work smarter, not harder.

No more emailing files to yourself or dealing with the Cloud. Quick Share lets you transfer photos, videos, documents, or entire folders between your Android and Windows devices with ease. Need edits on the go? Share back to your phone.

To get started, download and install Quick Share onto your Windows device.

Share with your Windows PC

Work smarter, not harder.

No more emailing files to yourself or dealing with the Cloud. Quick Share lets you transfer photos, videos, documents, or entire folders between your Android and Windows devices with ease. Need edits on the go? Share back to your phone.

To get started, download and install Quick Share onto your Windows device.

Learn more

Get started with Quick Share

How to use Quick Share on Android.

1. Open content in any app
2. Tap “Share,” then “Quick Share”
3. Select the device(s) to share with
4. Await acceptance from the recipient

Get started with Quick Share

How to use Quick Share on Windows.

1. Download and install the Quick Share app on your Windows PC
2. Sign in and enable “Quick Share” in your settings
3. Choose a file and select “Quick Share”
4. Select the device(s) to share with
5. Await acceptance from the recipient

Get started with Quick Share

How to use Quick Share on Chromebooks.

1. Enable “Quick Share” in your settings
2. Right-click on a file, then tap “Share”
3. Select the device to share with
4. Await acceptance from the recipient

Fast Pair.
Ready. Set. Pair.

Headphones to phone

Tech that keeps up with your pace.

Hitting the gym? Jumping on a call with a friend? Connect your Bluetooth headphones or speakers with your phone faster than ever. Choose from over 400 headphones with Fast Pair*.

Plus, with Fast Pair you can:
• Find your buds with Find My Device
• Get notifications on battery level
• Seamlessly switch between calls, movies and more, across devices

*Your phone or tablet is using Android 6.0 or higher. Your phone or tablet has Bluetooth. Location turned on for Android 11 or below.

Audio switching

Audio that moves with you.

Music playing while you cook, then a phone call comes in? Audio switch has you covered. Your headphones seamlessly switch between devices, transitioning smoothly to your call. When you're done, jump right back into your playlist.*

*Audio switch is supported on devices running Android 8 and above with Google Play Services. Your audio switch enabled headphones must be connected through Fast Pair to the same Google Account on each audio source like an Android phone or a tablet.

Fast Pair with Android Auto

Get connected. Get going.

With Bluetooth enabled, all you need to do is tap once on your phone screen, and your phone will automatically connect with your car. This allows you to quickly get going with Android Auto where you can navigate, call, chat, listen to media, and more.*

*Requires vehicle with Android Auto. Works with compatible devices. Devices sold separately.

Phone Hub

Respond to texts right from your Chromebook.

Phone in the other room? That’s OK. Use Phone Hub to read and respond to texts and messages, see what you were searching, turn on the Wi-Fi hotspot, check your phone’s battery life and more.

Unknown tracker alerts

Stay safe on the go.

Your Android device can now automatically detect and notify you of unfamiliar tracking devices (like Bluetooth tracker tags) moving with you, so you can take action to locate and disable them.

Detection works with compatible trackers. Location services and Bluetooth may need to be turned on. Requires cell service. Available on Android 6+ in all regions and languages that Android supports.

Learn more
Digital car key

Unlock your car with your phone.

With digital car key, you can unlock, lock and start a compatible car using just your phone. You're also able to securely share your digital car key with family and friends.
